# Vite reads environment variables from this directory (frontend/.env) by default.
# From the repo root, create or update the root .env if needed:
#   cp .env.example .env
# Then, from this directory, create frontend/.env for Vite using this example:
#   cp .env.example .env
# Keep the values in ../.env and ./.env in sync so the frontend sees the expected config.
